1
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,800
Mr. Glam, these are the flight attendants under my supervision.

2
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,280
Everyone’s here today.

3
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:17,440
Let’s go ahead and announce the results of our airline’s vote.

4
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:21,440
The award for Employee of the Year goes to…

5
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,040
You’re the cop who came to arrest me...

6
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,920
I’m glad you still remember.

7
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,000
So this was all part of Glam's plan, wasn’t it?

8
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,400
Well, you're not stupid after all.

9
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,600
I’m going to kill you.

10
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,920
This drug affects the nervous system.

11
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,920
You’re done, Glam!

12
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,280
Have some water first.

13
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,280
We’re going to be talking for a long time.

14
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:47,120
So this is Khun Glam?

15
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,640
Yes.

16
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:52,120
This is the real Khun Glam.

17
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:55,000
I'd always thought Khun Glam was a man.

18
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,440
Or maybe the name is Glammelia?

19
00:01:58,440 --> 00:02:01,640
Or maybe it’s Glam-ma?

20
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,640
Glam-ma...

21
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,160
Glam-ma...

22
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:07,760
Read my lips clearly...Glam-ma!

23
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,760
Wait, this is no time for a language lesson.

24
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,480
This is why no one has seen Khun Glam's face before.

25
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,960
But Khun Glam looks kind.

26
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:21,600
She is kind.
I asked her to take a pic with me and she didn't mind.

27
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,240
We were like "Cheese!".

28
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:28,400
So what we've heard about her
running a shady business and being a brutal mafia...

29
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,920
isn't true.

30
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:32,400
Exactly! With such a sweet face like this!

31
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:39,560
But what about you two saying Khun Glam sent people to kill you?

32
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,880
Is that even true?

33
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,680
I’m starting to doubt it now.

34
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:45,400
From the looks, she probably never even killed an ant.

35
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:46,720
Hmm.

36
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,720
Same thought here.

37
00:02:47,720 --> 00:02:50,640
She doesn’t seem like someone who could put Madam Porn in jail.

38
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:54,640
Honestly, maybe we just imagined the whole thing ourselves.

39
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:06,520
Hello, Khun Glam.

40
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,840
What was that again?

41
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,440
Of course! Sure!

42
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:11,160
Tonight?

43
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,720
Alright, I will tell everyone.

44
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,480
See you tonight, Khun Glam.

45
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,680
Chai, why was Khun Glam calling?

46
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:20,680
She said she's going to throw a party tonight for all of us!

47
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:26,040
Party, party, party!!!

48
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:29,120
So we’ll finally get to see Khun Glam in person?

49
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:33,120
Not likely, idiot.
How did you even become a flight attendant?

50
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,280
Chaba, you're so harsh!

51
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:48,560
This is the first time I feel like the food here actually tastes good.

52
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:51,040
That means you’re getting used to it, huh?

53
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:56,200
No, I’ll never get used to being here.

54
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,160
I’ll never get used to this!

55
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,160
I want freedom!

56
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:04,960
Madam.

57
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,480
Hmm?

58
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,800
I have hot news to tell you.

59
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,800
What news?

60
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,680
Hey!

61
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,440
Siri, how did you sneak a phone in here?

62
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,320
I paid a friend to smuggle it in.

63
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,440
Are you crazy?
If anyone sees, it’s a huge problem.

64
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,320
Forget it, Madam.

65
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:21,320
Here, look at this email sent to our company.

66
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:26,520
Khun Glam, the owner of Glamorous Airline,
announced a policy change.

67
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,520
Profits increased by forty percent.

68
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,720
Why did you let me see it, just to rub salt in the wound?

69
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,480
I’m not just showing you the email.

70
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:37,480
Look at the picture below, here!

71
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,800
This is Khun Glam!

72
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,920
You, Glam!

73
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:52,120
You’re the one who made me end up like this!

74
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:53,400
You, Glam!

75
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,160
Glam!

76
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,480
Why didn’t it break?

77
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,480
You’re not the Hulk, Madam.

78
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:07,880
Glam!

79
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:09,880
What’s all this noise?
Why aren't you eating?

80
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,720
Prisoner Porn, you have visitors.

81
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,720
Huh?

82
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,720
Come quickly, hurry!

83
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,600
Okay.

84
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,280
Are you thinking about what to eat?

85
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:42,280
I was just looking at the lights, they’re beautiful.

86
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,520
Tid-Gift, you’re dressed so flashy today.

87
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:47,840
Yeah.

88
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:48,400
Why?

89
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,560
You're stealing the spotlight from everyone else.

90
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,240
Yeah.

91
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,080
We're ready now.

92
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,600
Let’s toast!

93
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,760
Oops!

94
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,280
Chaba, you’re so clumsy.

95
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:59,240
I didn't mean to.

96
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,240
Mind your step, please.

97
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,360
Everyone!

98
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:03,440
Oh!

99
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:06,440
Khun Glam, these are the flight attendants under my supervision.

100
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,920
Hello.

101
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:12,720
Hello, I’m Sky.

102
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:16,720
Wow, the real Khun Glam is so lovely.

103
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,440
Thank you.

104
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,440
Are you not having a wedgie anymore?

105
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,280
I’m Tid-Gift, we’ve met before.

106
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:33,280
Of course I remember, you look stunning tonight.

107
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,240
I’m Chaba.

108
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:37,680
Your makeup is gorgeous.

109
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,680
Thank you, Khun Glam.

110
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,680
I’m All-New, nice to meet you.

111
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:45,080
Nice to meet you too.

112
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,520
I’m Kreetha, I'll be in your care.

113
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:50,080
Sorry, what was that?
This is no daycare!

114
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,280
Huh?

115
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,960
Just kidding.

116
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,960
Oh...

117
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:01,880
Happy to meet and work with you all.

118
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:05,880
Would you like some whiskey, Khun Glam?
This is the finest from Scotland.

119
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,680
No, thank you.

120
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:10,680
Or perhaps some French wine?

121
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,560
We’ve prepared it too.

122
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,560
Actually, I don’t drink alcohol.

123
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,600
Then may I ask what you’d like to drink?

124
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,600
Pink milk.

125
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,520
I've already prepared it.

126
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:25,520
Really?
Thank you so much.

127
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:31,400
Sky, where did you even get that?

128
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,360
Exactly.

129
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:36,360
Today, I also brought a little something for everyone.

130
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,680
They must be luxury brand gifts!

131
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,760
Thank you.

132
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:45,440
What is that?

133
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,280
Oh, honey

134
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,200
Why didn’t I get any?

135
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,840
Yours is extra special.

136
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:02,560
To make up for the wedgie...

137
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,160
Oh!

138
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:06,120
That bag is huge, bigger than anyone else’s.

139
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:09,880
I deserve it!
I'm the crew of the year!

140
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:13,880
This is not just bottled honey like the rest of you.

141
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:17,880
What’s inside?
It must be an expensive designer bag.

142
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:27,160
Oh wow, that's so Be-len-cia-ga!

143
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,360
Did you go trekking for this, Khun Glam?

144
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:36,160
Yes, I climbed and picked it just for you.

145
00:08:36,160 --> 00:08:38,160
You climbed and picked it yourself?
Thank you so much.

146
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:43,120
Well then, since everyone’s here.

147
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:46,120
Let’s go ahead and announce the results of our airline’s vote.

148
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:49,280
The Crew of the Year vote, right?

149
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,200
Yes.

150
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:54,520
Yay, I’m so excited, it must be me!

151
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:58,000
I’m the hardest worker, I never took a single day off!

152
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Oh, it has to be me!

153
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,080
Who are you two?

154
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,080
I don’t recognize you.

155
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,960
But you’re pretty.

156
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:20,000
You might not know me.

157
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:24,000
But you definitely know my sister well.

158
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,920
Wait, you’re the cop who came to arrest me...

159
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:34,360
How are you? I'm glad you still remember.

160
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,520
What do you want?

161
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,720
Nothing much.

162
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:40,720
I just wanted to visit, see how you’re doing in prison.

163
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:44,360
So this was all part of Glam's plan, wasn’t it?

164
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,760
Oh, do I look that suspicious?

165
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,960
Answer! Yes or no.

166
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,320
Well, you're not stupid after all.

167
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,920
Hey, you two really are Glam’s people!

168
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,600
Don’t think...

169
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,800
I’ll give in so easily this time.

170
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,560
And don’t think you’re getting out.

171
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,080
I heard you’re in for life.

172
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:11,360
You bastards! You rotten people!

173
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,400
Our job is done.

174
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:17,920
We finally locked the rival airline’s owner away for life.

175
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:22,320
And Khun Glam will surely reward us big time.

176
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,680
You rotten people!

177
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:28,440
Excuse me, from now on you won’t be bothered again.

178
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,440
You!

179
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:43,040
Glam! I’ll kill you! I’ll kill you!

180
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,960
The host is so handsome.

181
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,160
Thank you, thank you.

182
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,600
Khun Glam is adorable.

183
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,720
Thank you.

184
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:58,320
And today, we’re not just here for a party.

185
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:00,800
Khun Glam also has special awards.

186
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:04,800
For the top-voted employees on our page.

187
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:09,200
And from votes among coworkers in the company.

188
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:12,880
And I have the results right here.

189
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,480
Oh, I’m so excited!

190
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,120
The first award...

191
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:22,120
Outstanding Service Employee goes to…

192
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,400
Tid-Gift!

193
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,200
Hey! Tid-Gift! Tid-Gift!

194
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,440
Thank you!

195
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,720
Would you like to say a few words?

196
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:42,440
Thank you Khun Glam, thank you Glamorous Airline.

197
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:45,440
Thank you everyone for voting.
I’m gorgeous, that’s all, goodbye!

198
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:51,200
What the...?

199
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:51,760
Well, she's gorgeous.

200
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:57,200
Next award, Outstanding Communication Employee goes to…

201
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,520
Must be me!

202
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,320
All-New!

203
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,960
Please come say a few words, All-New.

204
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,200
Thank you so, so much.

205
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,880
I never thought I’d win this award.

206
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:20,400
I want to thank all of my crew mates.

207
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:22,960
I want to thank every captain that's ever flew with me.

208
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,680
I wanna thank the dinosaurs that died to make a petroleum.

209
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,560
And the jet fuel that's in the jets.

210
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,720
I wanna thank Bernoulli.

211
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,680
For figuring out the differential air pressure...

212
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,320
and it creates upper lift in the wind.

213
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,440
I wanna thank the dogs...

214
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:36,120
at the 7-Eleven I go to...for always being so nice!

215
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:38,000
Alright, stop, stop, stop!

216
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,720
Whoever can translate that for me, tell me after the party!

217
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:41,720
Alright, please...

218
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,960
Okay, next award...

219
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,280
the third award.

220
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:51,280
Outstanding Courtesy Employee goes to…

221
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:51,960
Me?

222
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:52,160
Me!

223
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,800
Our dear Kreetha!

224
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:00,080
Alright, put that down.

225
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,720
Excuse me.

226
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,840
Thank you very much.

227
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,560
Thank you everyone.

228
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:11,200
Thank you to all the people.

229
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,760
From every direction.

230
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,440
Stop. Move on!

231
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:16,000
Uh...please say a few words.

232
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,360
Yes, of course.

233
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,520
Thank you very much for this award.

234
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:22,520
Love me less, but love me longer...

235
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,600
We love Kreetha! We love Kreetha!

236
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:34,000
Wow, the next award makes so much sense.

237
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:38,000
The award for Most Cheerful Employee with the Brightest Smile goes to...

238
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,040
Chaba!

239
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,240
I'm very cheerful!

240
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,040
Thank you, Khun Glam.

241
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,040
You're always cheerful, always smiling!

242
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:52,920
Please, Chaba, a few words.

243
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,920
Thank you for this award.
And thank you, Uncle Tong.

244
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:59,000
Uncle Tong? Who’s that?

245
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,400
My neighbor.
He raised me when I was a kid.

246
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,880
And thank you to Aunt Joy and Aunt Koi too.

247
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,440
Who are Joy and Koi?

248
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,040
The owners of the women’s dorm.

249
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:11,080
The dorm was called Sathittham,
three thousand baht per month.

250
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:14,960
They taught me manners, smiling, all those things.

251
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,960
Thank you.

252
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,680
Thank you.

253
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,600
Now, the final award.

254
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,440
I must say, this one is absolutely perfect.

255
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:28,440
The Employee of the Year award goes to…

256
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,440
Must be me again...

257
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,440
Sky!

258
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,400
Sky!

259
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:38,880
Go, girl!

260
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,840
So beautiful!

261
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,440
Oh my God!

262
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,800
Oh my God!

263
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:58,960
Thank you.

264
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:01,960
Thank...

265
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:06,600
Hello, hello, hello...

266
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,600
The mic isn’t working.

267
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,480
It seems like the mic is broken.

268
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:12,400
No worries.
You did your best.

269
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,400
Please step down from the stage.

270
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,440
Thank you. This way, please.

271
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:21,320
But I prepared a long thank-you speech...

272
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,200
Come on, down you go.

273
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:23,240
What the hell?

274
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:27,240
I must congratulate everyone who won awards tonight.

275
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:29,960
But that’s not all.

276
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:33,960
Tonight, we also have an exclusive,
very special performance from Khun Glam!

277
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,840
Are you ready, Khun Glam?

278
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:40,400
I’m ready.

279
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,400
Cue the music!

280
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,640
That's fabulous!

281
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:04,760
She's so adorable!

282
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:06,040
Let’s have some fun!

283
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:50,040
Who could it be, Madam?

284
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,440
It's so early.

285
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:53,880
Exactly.

286
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:57,440
That’s the person who came to see you.

287
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,680
Wait, who is this?
I don’t know him.

288
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,800
Siri, you go talk.

289
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,520
No, Madam, you do it.

290
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:05,320
But he’s the one who came to bail you two out.

291
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:06,840
Huh?

292
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:08,840
Talk to him yourselves, then go get changed.

293
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,880
What kind of joke is this?

294
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:24,280
This is not a joke.
I came to bail you two out.

295
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,320
And who are you?

296
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:27,720
I’m Khun Glam’s lawyer.

297
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,920
Glam?

298
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,920
I was assigned to post bail for both of you.

299
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,880
Once you’re done here...

300
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:36,880
Khun Glam would like to meet you.

301
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:42,440
Follow this, all the details are inside.

302
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:50,760
Wait a second, Madam.
What exactly is Glam trying to do?

303
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:54,760
He framed us, and now he’s bailing us out...
why?

304
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:59,520
It just means...
he wants to show he can do whatever he wants with us.

305
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:03,280
Is that true, Madam?

306
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:05,960
I’m like a chick in his hand.

307
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,640
If he squeezes, I die.

308
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:10,440
If he loosens, I live.

309
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,440
But I won’t let him treat me like that ever again!

310
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,040
Hey!

311
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,120
Hey!

312
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,120
Chai, your face!

313
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:34,480
Your face too!

314
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:39,440
Don’t tell me you got stung by the bees
from the honeycomb Khun Glam gave Sky...

315
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,680
That’s right.

316
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:44,280
I asked to see it, I thought it was empty.

317
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:48,280
Are you crazy? She literally said the bees were fresh from the hive,
and you still wanted to see it?

318
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:51,640
Well, you got stung too, so don’t act tough.

319
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,440
I just wanted to be part of it.

320
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,440
I didn’t want to be left out.

321
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:01,520
Wait...Kreetha, you got stung too?

322
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:03,520
Yes, I just wanted to see real bees up close.

323
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,880
Good thing...none of us are allergic to bee stings.

324
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,600
Yeah, lucky no one’s seriously hurt.

325
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,720
I think someone is.

326
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:14,760
Hey!

327
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:15,200
Hey!

328
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:16,920
I got a headache.

329
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:17,880
I got a fever.

330
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:18,840
...stomachache...

331
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:19,840
...joint pain...

332
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,160
...chills...

333
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,120
Does that mean I’m allergic?

334
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,120
That's obvious!

335
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,800
Sky, sit down, sit down!

336
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:29,680
But why is it that when Khun Glam climbed up to get it...

337
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,440
she didn’t get stung at all?

338
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:32,280
That's true.

339
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:35,120
Yeah, Khun Glam looked totally fine.

340
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:37,040
No bite marks, no stings anywhere.

341
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:41,040
That’s exactly why someone like her deserves to lead this company.

342
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:44,160
That's true.
She's strong, just like a real leader.

343
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:44,960
Yeah.

344
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,640
Well, I think I need a leader too.

345
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:47,440
Lead you where?

346
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:50,320
Lead me to the hospital!

347
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:53,480
Oh no, she’s burning up!
Must be a fever.

348
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,480
Call an ambulance, quick!

349
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:56,960
Sky! Sky!

350
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,400
You got out pretty fast, Madam.

351
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,840
Only two weeks after me.

352
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,240
Where’s the stuff I ordered?

353
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,000
I’ve got it right here, Madam.

354
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,480
I wouldn’t dare cross you.

355
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,960
You’d just hire people to beat me up again.

356
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:19,120
Where’s the stuff?

357
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:23,600
This drug affects the nervous system.
Once you take it, you’ll feel it.

358
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,400
Good.

359
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:32,000
Five thousand.
Don’t just sit there, Madam.

360
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,640
I’ll transfer you ten thousand.

361
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:34,640
Wow.

362
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,520
You’re still generous, just like when we were inside.

363
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:38,920
I’ll get going then.

364
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:39,920
Don’t forget to transfer.

365
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,600
Glam, you're done!

366
00:20:57,080 --> 00:20:58,800
Hello.

367
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,840
Finally, we meet.

368
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,560
So you’re Glam, right?

369
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:05,920
Sorry to keep you waiting.

370
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,640
It’s fine.

371
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:11,160
I honestly thought you were a man all along.

372
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:13,160
Am I pretty, then?

373
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:21,600
You must be tired from traveling.
Please, Have some water first.

374
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:22,720
Thank you.

375
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,280
We’re going to be talking for a long time.

376
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:27,080
You must be furious with me now.

377
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:30,120
And you think everything that happened was because of me, right?

378
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:31,440
Smart of you...

379
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,440
But I want you to look at this first.

380
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:41,520
These are files from Porn Airline that were sent to me.

381
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:43,920
I never sent them.

382
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:47,920
And you think the info you received was from me?

383
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,720
Oh no, Madam. Oh no!

384
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,200
What is it, Siri?

385
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:57,520
Madam, we just got an email from Glamorous Airline.

386
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,400
What email?

387
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:03,400
It’s their profit reports.
I don’t know why they sent it to us.

388
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:08,840
To mock us, obviously!
Our airline is losing money.

389
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,680
Damn you, Glam!

390
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:15,160
But the actual numbers for Glamorous Airline...

391
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:17,680
aren’t much higher than Porn Airline.

392
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,920
Are you saying...

393
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:22,600
both of our companies have been manipulated?

394
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:26,600
Yes. I think someone is behind all of this.

395
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,520
That can’t be.

396
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:30,400
You saw the files yourself.

397
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:33,960
The data we received was fake.

398
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:36,960
Someone definitely set us up.

399
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,560
And how am I supposed to trust you?

400
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,600
Glam, you’ll never defeat Porn Airline!

401
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,840
I’ll scalp you and tear you apart piece by piece!

402
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:55,400
Wait, I never said that!

403
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,600
It’s AI. It was made and someone...

404
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,560
kept sending it to me.

405
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,840
What? Seriously?

406
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,560
Once we learned you were framed,

407
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:07,760
we knew someone was messing with our heads.

408
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:10,720
But who? And why?

409
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:14,000
Honestly, I don’t know who they are.

410
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,840
I only wanted to help you out.

411
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:16,840
But if you don’t believe me...

412
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:21,160
Here. This is all the information.

413
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:23,160
I hope you understand me.

414
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Goodbye.

415
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:42,480
All-New, where are you?
Come here, I need your help.

416
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,760
What’s this drink, Madam?
It’s so refreshing.

417
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,640
Hey! Siri!

418
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:55,560
Hey! Siri!

419
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:00,280
Oh no, Siri! Siri!

420
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:03,960
Siri, oh dear!

421
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:05,960
Oh no, Siri, oh my...

422
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:16,400
The job’s done.

423
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,200
Finally, we can travel with peace of mind.

424
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:21,720
By now, Madam Porn must be eating prison food for life.

425
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,480
And she must be holding a serious grudge against Glamorous.

426
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:27,600
Well, can’t help it.
She was too easy to manipulate.

427
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:31,120
She even sent her people into Glamorous Airline.

428
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:36,760
Sorry, you didn’t pass.

429
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:40,240
So...I wasn’t selected to be a flight attendant here?

430
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:42,240
And that’s exactly the reason you didn’t pass.

431
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,440
Please.

432
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,760
Thank you.

433
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:53,760
So dumb!
I told him he didn’t pass, and he still asked again.

434
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:57,880
Beam, are you tired from work?

435
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:00,040
I bought you some snacks.

436
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,000
Oh, thank you, Peck!

437
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,440
I remember you really love this shop.

438
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,840
I lined up for ages to get it.

439
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:08,080
Wow.

440
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:09,080
Is it the flavor you like?

441
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:09,440
Yes.

442
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:10,000
Right?

443
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,160
It looks so yummy, Peck.

444
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:13,520
I remember your favorite flavor.

445
00:25:13,520 --> 00:25:14,520
There are lots of flavors here.

446
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,600
And making Madam Porn believe...

447
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,960
that Glamorous Airline was suspicious,

448
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:23,480
involved in shady businesses,

449
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:25,920
and linked to crime...

450
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:26,920
That made everything even easier.

451
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,000
What the hell?

452
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,520
Hey, hey!

453
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,440
That guy’s such a coward!

454
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,520
Screaming and running like that...

455
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,120
Man, this corpse is gorgeous.

456
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:57,240
Wait, not as gorgeous as your sister.

457
00:25:57,240 --> 00:25:58,240
The real beauty is right here.

458
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:03,920
Now that we’ve done our job and ruined Porn Airline completely...

459
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:05,600
our boss must be thrilled.

460
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:06,960
Of course he is.

461
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:09,280
We just eliminated one airline competitor.

462
00:26:09,280 --> 00:26:11,360
Wait.

463
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,320
There’s still Glamorous left.

464
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:17,320
That was you!
You infiltrated but messed it up.

465
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:18,960
How was I supposed to know...

466
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:22,120
that nerd would trace everything back to me?

467
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:26,120
But we turned it around, didn’t we?
We used him as a tool to extract intel.

468
00:26:27,360 --> 00:26:28,360
Should we just kill him?

469
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:32,080
No need. I have another way.

470
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:39,280
The camera on his glasses...

471
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:40,640
what did it capture?

472
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,720
Nothing useful.

473
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:44,040
All day he just talks to ants and mosquitoes.

474
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,040
What? Let me see.

475
00:26:47,840 --> 00:26:50,200
Oh, Steve! Long time no see.

476
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,200
Where are you building your nest?

477
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:55,880
Hey Peter, have you eaten yet?
Haven’t seen you in days.

478
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:58,880
Wow, nice mustache today.
Going somewhere fancy?

479
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:03,320
Is he gathering intel or just wasting time?

480
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:05,320
All he does is watch bugs.

481
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:07,160
No wonder he's a nerd.

482
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:10,480
He was staring at birds until one crashed into his glasses and broke them.

483
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:14,320
Are those new glasses?
They look just like the old ones.

484
00:27:14,320 --> 00:27:18,320
I followed him.
He bought twelve pairs of the exact same glasses.

485
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:22,480
What?
So now I have to attach the camera to all of them?

486
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:24,160
Forget it.

487
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:27,480
We’ll find another way to deal with him later.

488
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,480
Fine.

489
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:32,920
Let’s just go blow some money and have fun first.
Let’s go!

490
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:45,160
Siri! Siri, are you okay?

491
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:47,160
I already called an ambulance, Siri!

492
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,600
Siri!

493
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:56,600
No, no...

494
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:58,440
I don't understand.

495
00:27:58,440 --> 00:27:59,440
Stop talking now.

496
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,440
Stop!

497
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:09,160
How did things end up like this?

498
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:13,160
I’m the one who caused this...that's why Siri's like this...

499
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:16,920
Siri.

500
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,000
Get the patient onto the stretcher.

501
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:27,120
No, not me! Her!

502
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:28,280
We saw you crying, we thought you were the patient.

503
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:28,920
Her!

504
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:29,920
Oh! Right, right!

505
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:33,800
Siri, please don’t leave me!

506
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:40,400
Siri!

507
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,560
All-New! All-New!

508
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:49,320
What’s wrong with Siri?

509
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,600
No wonder I didn’t see you all when I went to the prison.

510
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:52,840
When did you get out?

511
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:55,200
Glam bailed me out.

512
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,200
Khun Glam?

513
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:58,760
Yes. At first, I planned to poison her.

514
00:28:58,760 --> 00:29:00,520
But Glam told me...

515
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:02,280
both Porn Airline and Glamorous…

516
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:04,360
we’re being manipulated.

517
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,200
By who?

518
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,480
I don’t know.

519
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:10,480
And then Siri...she accidentally drank the poisoned water I meant for Glam.

520
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:15,080
All-New, is it possible that inside Glamorous...

521
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:17,080
I wasn't the only one who sent you in?

522
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:23,880
Here...there must be some information.

523
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,640
check it and see what’s inside.

524
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,160
Glam gave it to me herself.

525
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:30,640
Alright. I’ll check it.

526
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:32,400
I need to go see Siri first.

527
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,400
Siri...oh, Siri!

528
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:49,360
Thank you so much for watching over the company.

529
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,800
It’s my duty.

530
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:52,640
You’re the sweetest.

531
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:56,640
Now that you have revealed yourself, I feel more at ease.

532
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:02,560
Khun Glam, here are the documents you requested.

533
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:04,080
Thank you, Tid-Gift.

534
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,560
Such a small matter, this is easy for me.

535
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,800
You work quickly, Tid-Gift.

536
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:08,600
